import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='rate', by='state', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of rate across all states?')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='State', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('state')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    data_grouped = data_grouped.sort_values('rate', ascending=False)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(data_grouped['state'], data_grouped['rate'], color='b', alpha=0.7)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest rate?', wrap=True)
    
    max_rate = data_grouped['rate'].max()
    max_state = data_grouped.loc[data_grouped['rate'] == max_rate, 'state'].iloc[0]
    plt.axhline(max_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Rate: {max_state} ({max_rate:.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('state')['rate'].agg(['min', 'max'])
    data_grouped['range'] = data_grouped['max'] - data_grouped['min']
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data_grouped['range'].plot(kind='bar', ax=ax, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    
    plt.title('What is the range of rate for each state?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Rate Range')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Rate Range'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
